Key Match Events: Kody Clemens hit a two-run homer to lift the Philadelphia Phillies to a 4-2 win over the Toronto Blue Jays.
Cristopher Sanchez allowed two runs over seven quality innings.
Kyle Schwarber hit a leadoff home run for the second consecutive day.
J.T. Realmuto added a home run in the ninth inning.
Brendon Little, Tommy Nance, and Ryan Burr came on in relief of Francis.
Pre-Game Insights: Bowden Francis has become a regular fixture in the Blue Jays' rotation, earning five wins in six starts.
Francis allowed three runs on six hits but struck out six over six innings against Philadelphia.
Vladimir Guerrero Jr. and Alejandro Kirk had back-to-back RBI doubles in the first inning for a brief Toronto lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Francis said he is getting into a routine of starting, good or bad, and can hone in every five days.
Harper left the game after the first inning with a left elbow contusion after being hit by a pitch.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Clemens's two-run homer lifted the Phillies to a 4-2 win on Wednesday for a two-game sweep in Toronto.
Schwarber's 32nd home run of the season came a day after he hit three homers and drove in six runs in Philadelphia's 10-9 come-from-behind victory over the Blue Jays.
Realmuto's 12th homer of the year came on an 84.3 m.p.h. slider from Burr.
